To add the import rule for the pattern `'**/../storefront/**'` with the specified message, you need to modify the `importRules` object in your ESLint configuration. Here's how you can update it:

```javascript
const importRules = {
  paths: [
    {
      name: '@otovo/shared/cloudConfig/config.json',
      message: 'Please import from cloudConfig/cloudConfig.js instead',
    },
  ],
  patterns: [
    {
      group: ['**/cloudConfig/config.json'],
      message: 'Please import from cloudConfig/cloudConfig.js instead',
    },
    {
      group: ['**/../storefront/**'],
      message: "Don't import things from storefront. Use @otovo/shared for shared modules, and ensure imports are a DAG",
    },
  ],
};
```

In this updated configuration:

1. We've changed the `patterns` property from an array of strings to an array of objects.
2. We've kept the existing rule for `**/cloudConfig/config.json` and added a new rule for `**/../storefront/**`.
3. Each pattern object now has a `group` property (which contains the pattern) and a `message` property.

This configuration will now trigger the specified error message when ESLint detects an import matching the `**/../storefront/**` pattern.

Make sure to replace the existing `importRules` object in your configuration file with this updated version. The rest of your ESLint configuration can remain the same.
